Here are the main categories of Nmap scripts:

auth: Scripts related to authentication
broadcast: Scripts that use broadcast packets
brute: Password-cracking scripts
default: Default scripts included with Nmap
discovery: Discovery-related scripts (e.g., finding hosts)
dos: Denial-of-service attack scripts
exploit: Exploit scripts
fuzzer: Fuzzing scripts
intrusive: Intrusive scripts (may cause disruptions)
malware: Malware detection scripts
safe: Safe scripts (less likely to cause issues)
version: Version detection scripts
